<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Harlem Plaza Redesign</title>
  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background: #1f1f1f;
      color: #fff;
    }

    header {
      height: 100vh;
      background: url('hero.jpg') center/cover no-repeat;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
    }

    header h1 {
      font-size: 3rem;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    nav {
      position: fixed;
      top: 0;
      width: 100%;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.7);
      padding: 10px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    nav a {
      color: white;
      margin: 0 15px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    section {
      padding: 60px 20px;
      max-width: 1000px;
      margin: auto;
    }

    .alt {
      background: #2a2a2a;
    }

    img {
      width: 100%;
      border-radius: 10px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
      gap: 20px;
    }

    footer {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 20px;
      background: #111;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<nav>
  <a href="#home">Home</a>
  <a href="#about">About</a>
  <a href="#problem">Problem</a>
  <a href="#site">Site</a>
  <a href="#design">Design</a>
  <a href="#final">Final</a>
  <a href="#reflection">Reflection</a>
</nav>

<header id="home">
  <h1>Harlem Plaza Redesign</h1>
  <p>A Safer, Greener Community Space</p>
</header>

<section id="about">
  <h2>About the Project</h2>
  <p>This project explores how Montefiore Square can be redesigned into a safer and more welcoming public space. The goal is to improve pedestrian experience, increase greenery, and create a strong sense of community.</p>
</section>

<section id="problem" class="alt">
  <h2>The Problem</h2>
  <p>The current plaza lacks seating, greenery, and safe pedestrian crossings. It is underused and does not serve the needs of the surrounding community.</p>
</section>

<section id="site">
  <h2>Site Context</h2>
  <p>The plaza is located in a busy urban environment with heavy traffic flow. Pedestrian movement is not prioritized, and accessibility is limited.</p>
  <img src="site.jpg" alt="Site Image">
</section>

<section id="design" class="alt">
  <h2>Design Options</h2>
  <div class="grid">
    <div>
      <h3>Option 1: Green Plaza</h3>
      <img src="design1.jpg">
      <p>Focus on trees, shade, and relaxation.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3>Option 2: Market Plaza</h3>
      <img src="design2.jpg">
      <p>Includes vendor kiosks and activity spaces.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="final">
  <h2>Final Proposal</h2>
  <p>The final design combines greenery with flexible community space, improving safety and usability.</p>
  <img src="final.jpg">
</section>

<section id="reflection" class="alt">
  <h2>Reflection</h2>
  <p>AI tools helped generate design ideas and visualize possibilities. However, human decision-making was essential in selecting and refining the final proposal.</p>
</section>

<footer>
  <p>Midterm Project | Urban Design</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
